Washington Nationals company description

The Washington Nationals are a Major League Baseball team based in Washington, D.C. The Nationals are a member of the East Division of MLB’s National League. Nationals Park, located on the Anacostia River in Southeast Washington, was the first Major League Baseball stadium in America to earn the LEED-certified Silver designation by the U.S. Green Building Council. World Series Champions: 2019 NL East Champions: 2012, 2014, 2016, 2017 For ticket information, visit Nationals.com or call (202) 675-NATS (6287). View our employment opportunities at nationals.com/careers Also visit us at: • Facebook.com/Nationals • Twitter.com/Nationals • Instagram.com/Nationals
